t-earnings call.\n\nMany industrial power users and tech sector experts are signing agreements to\nensure their facilities can access zero-carbon and reliable nuclear energy now\nand into the future, he said.\n\nOverall, power use from the thousands of giant computing warehouses that\ncomprise data centers is expected to triple globally from less than 15\nterawatt-hours (TWh) in 2023 to 46 TWh this year, according to Morgan Stanley\nResearch.\n\n(By Mrinalika Roy; Editing by Shilpi Majumdar)\n\n  * Share\n\n### Mining.com Recommends\n\n#### Li-FT touts best lithium assay yet at target near Yellowknife\n\nThe company is eyeing an initial resource for Q3.\n\nBlair McBride | April 30, 2024 | 9:45 am\n\n#### Highlander Silver gets funding for new project bought from SSR Mining\n\nFunding has been negotiated with members of the Lundin family as well as\nCanadian mining billionaires Richard Warke and Eric Sprott.\n\nStaff Writer | April 30, 2024 | 8:44 am\n\n#### G-7 nations to agree on first half of 2030s for coal phase-out\n\nThe US, UK, Germany, France, Canada, Japan and Italy agreed on the date after\ntalks on Monday held under Italy\u2019s presidency.\n\nBloomberg News | April 30, 2024 | 8:26 am\n\n#### NexGen Energy rises on $130 million offering in Australia\n\nThe company has also amended the at-the-market program announced in December.\n\nStaff Writer | April 30, 2024 | 6:05 am\n\n### Comments\n\n### Cancel reply\n\n### More News\n\n#### Flooding in Russia raises concerns of radioactive contamination in Tobol\nRiver\n\nStaff Writer | April 23, 2024 | 10:30 am\n\n#### Energy Fuels buys Base Resources for $240 million\n\nStaff Writer | April 22, 2024 | 2:24 pm\n\n#### GoviEx plunges as Niger uranium project faces junta deadline\n\nStaff Writer | April 19, 2024 | 8:42 am\n\n#### Berkeley to take uranium mine dispute with Spain to arbitration\n\nReuters | April 11, 2024 | 4:29 am\n\n  * Terms of Use\n  * About Us\n\n\u00a9 2024 The Northern Miner Group, All Rights Re